[Guest]: that's the very rough

00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:52.000
[Guest]: sketch of the peopling of the

00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:54.000
[Amit Varma]: world. You can, yeah.

00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:56.000
[Amit Varma]: And the other interesting thing is that

00:23:56.000 --> 00:23:58.000
[Amit Varma]: we weren't the, I mean those out of

00:23:58.000 --> 00:24:00.000
[Amit Varma]: migrants weren't the first humans here

00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:02.000
[Amit Varma]: that you know, I mean we are all of course

00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:04.000
[Amit Varma]: homo sapiens which are the only surviving human

00:24:04.000 --> 00:24:06.000
[Amit Varma]: species left but there were various other human species

00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:08.000
[Amit Varma]: across the world and what I kind of

00:24:08.000 --> 00:24:10.000
[Amit Varma]: found fascinating was where you mentioned that

00:24:10.000 --> 00:24:12.000
[Amit Varma]: homo sapiens in Africa

