[Amit Varma]: but everywhere else they went

00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:20.000
[Amit Varma]: they intermingled. For example

00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:22.000
[Amit Varma]: to quote again from your book

00:24:22.000 --> 00:24:24.000
[Amit Varma]: quote, all non-African

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:26.000
[Amit Varma]: homo sapiens today carry about 2%

00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:28.000
[Amit Varma]: Neanderthal genes in their DNA.

00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:30.000
[Amit Varma]: Some of us like the Melanesians, Papuans

00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:32.000
[Amit Varma]: and Aboriginal Australians also carry

00:24:32.000 --> 00:24:34.000
[Amit Varma]: 3-6% Denisovan DNA.

00:24:34.000 --> 00:24:36.000
[Amit Varma]: Because of the genetic inheritance

