[Amit Varma]: we may call them our ancestors

00:24:38.000 --> 00:24:40.000
[Amit Varma]: but it is perhaps more reasonable

00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:42.000
[Amit Varma]: to see them as our evolutionary cousins

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:44.000
[Amit Varma]: with whom homo sapiens

00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:46.000
[Amit Varma]: did dally.

00:24:46.000 --> 00:24:48.000
[Guest]: Stop quote. It only

00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:50.000
[Guest]: means that Neanderthals were present

00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:52.000
[Guest]: in Europe and Denisovans

00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:54.000
[Guest]: were present in Central Asia and those

00:24:54.000 --> 00:24:56.000
[Guest]: regions. And we partied with them.

00:24:56.000 --> 00:24:58.000
[Guest]: And we partied with them.

00:24:58.000 --> 00:25:00.000
[Guest]: But it doesn't mean that

00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:02.000
[Guest]: if Neanderthals were not in Africa

