[Guest]: they couldn't have mixed with Neanderthals. Exactly.

00:25:04.000 --> 00:25:06.000
[Guest]: But there were many more species of

00:25:06.000 --> 00:25:08.000
[Guest]: homo species in Africa

00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:10.000
[Guest]: than in outside of Africa.

00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:12.000
[Guest]: So it is a given

00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:14.000
[Guest]: that they would have mixed. In fact

00:25:14.000 --> 00:25:16.000
[Guest]: the beginning of the modern human

00:25:16.000 --> 00:25:18.000
[Guest]: himself would have been as a result of

00:25:18.000 --> 00:25:20.000
[Guest]: multiple mixtures between

00:25:20.000 --> 00:25:22.000
[Guest]: different species of the

00:25:22.000 --> 00:25:24.000
[Guest]: homo species. So it is just that

00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:26.000
[Guest]: in Africa you would not see

00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:28.000
[Guest]: evidence of mixing with Neanderthals

00:25:28.000 --> 00:25:30.000
[Guest]: or Denisovans because they were

00:25:30.000 --> 00:25:32.000
[Guest]: probably not in Africa. They were

00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:34.000
[Guest]: in those regions. And the

00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:36.000
[Guest]: out of Africa migrants came across them

00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:38.000
[Guest]: when they immigrated out of

00:25:38.000 --> 00:25:40.000
[Guest]: Africa. And they did mix with them.

00:25:40.000 --> 00:25:42.000
[Guest]: Must have mixed with them pretty early for all of us to have

00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:44.000
[Guest]: around 2% Neanderthal

00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:46.000
[Amit Varma]: ancestry. Marvellous. And

00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:48.000
[Amit Varma]: through all these years like before

00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:50.000
[Amit Varma]: we sort of come to modern

00:25:50.000 --> 00:25:52.000
[Amit Varma]: times of 7000 BC which is going

